[
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.1",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "I {am} the man {that} hath seen affliction by the rod of his wrath.",
    "hash": "f5ea797778911f7034f30a2023e367fd5ad095fc54edff4628959ffe1cad8783"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.2",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "He hath led me, and brought {me into} darkness, but not {into} light.",
    "hash": "c9436c91c474f3a0d016539ec47c9ebaddd84ef221b282d8dad21cec3005aa14"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.3",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "Surely against me is he turned; he turneth his hand {against me} all the day.",
    "hash": "45014df0c95a8e4d6046e409cf530feeba34ecee493c7cce1ac49a5d0308d613"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.4",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "My flesh and my skin hath he made old; he hath broken my bones.",
    "hash": "2e67a30cbb0b39caed38bcc1da63d7e70a69e5ca8acf8c5c935207669ea03ac6"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.5",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "He hath builded against me, and compassed {me} with gall and travail.",
    "hash": "0c4326d71f430d4975809c065e932256df6cdb44acea39d4c6dd73608deae9a5"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.6",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "He hath set me in dark places, as {they that be} dead of old.",
    "hash": "853f99fcfd56585ec430c3f2bd45a6b86537850b7d237ab7199ae25db6c87ca6"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.7",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "He hath hedged me about, that I cannot get out: he hath made my chain heavy.",
    "hash": "0487b8521002b34eb6e53ae67914569d74c895ff8e9465d271c7270ad7f1ce2a"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.8",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "Also when I cry and shout, he shutteth out my prayer.",
    "hash": "e0142635da6ae89edc1b5e4b6d4927fc72d120929e1b4af6ee57275d63f17348"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.9",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "He hath inclosed my ways with hewn stone, he hath made my paths crooked.",
    "hash": "3d5000f155857b59b5de4cfbd510c22c5fd5a831653f0998b69ba6cda738260f"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.10",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "He {was} unto me {as} a bear lying in wait, {and as} a lion in secret places.",
    "hash": "92215a3507a9514262d8d0bab095adae8c25887637447765ed80b8560dadfc90"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.11",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "He hath turned aside my ways, and pulled me in pieces: he hath made me desolate.",
    "hash": "253483c619cb83d430e096ac1fefcbfdb0f35c6837028502e361e32c37b2b0dc"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.12",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "He hath bent his bow, and set me as a mark for the arrow.",
    "hash": "7e395509813f1c6c8676ca446f0acc089cbe961d0694ff733f1da6095796433c"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.13",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "He hath caused the arrows of his quiver to enter into my reins. {arrows: Heb. sons}",
    "hash": "cdc687a9d337069545f87a7da248f868820385f9033a552727d006c864ab9024"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.14",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "I was a derision to all my people; {and} their song all the day.",
    "hash": "4d3581345ebdf67e97cd992ef2e8fa7d9960fabe236f9c63fe742b20fbb49e83"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.15",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "He hath filled me with bitterness, he hath made me drunken with wormwood. {bitterness: Heb. bitternesses}",
    "hash": "088cfc41cb3aca8ff3cfd8a3ff3c102b3f93f43488de0ce80b6d28f41609aed3"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.16",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "He hath also broken my teeth with gravel stones, he hath covered me with ashes. {covered...: or, rolled me in the ashes}",
    "hash": "29b28e0d7eb62f2ce37dec7cd0c1e03484a82288c4803567e09e2b5af4032d40"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.17",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "And thou hast removed my soul far off from peace: I forgat prosperity. {prosperity: Heb. good}",
    "hash": "75476c2c58e4ed6d812dfc9dbe1f7e0a0d6f0e2a2348c93f2b8a8fa2c8b7b25c"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.18",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "And I said, My strength and my hope is perished from the LORD:",
    "hash": "0114e03805de7289e8da86b565f173538b19d38d18d61aef4faa0c728c398919"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.19",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "Remembering mine affliction and my misery, the wormwood and the gall. {Remembering: or, Remember}",
    "hash": "bd68873aca91a95a23c0c4e447ac5dd6ee439769db6a60a0bc0bddfe6aa4db11"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.20",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "My soul hath {them} still in remembrance, and is humbled in me. {humbled: Heb. bowed}",
    "hash": "32eaa6b62e1a1c5d03f61ac30c28975e94c231d0881261b3e4cd1d1dcf7b4eff"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.21",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "This I recall to my mind, therefore have I hope. {recall...: Heb. make to return to my heart}",
    "hash": "7320b783888092780fda1443faaf59e8956a668187310016a5d9ad0816af90b6"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.22",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "{It is of} the LORD'S mercies that we are not consumed, because his compassions fail not.",
    "hash": "0dd9bff32dd3a25d7102df5ef3d3fcd992e771d2652a5272f329abf5083e0dc0"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.23",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "{They are} new every morning: great {is} thy faithfulness.",
    "hash": "3028a0c2ad59ddb3d472ae3773aac809621e8581ec47c5e6970be553dd14e246"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.24",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "The LORD {is} my portion, saith my soul; therefore will I hope in him.",
    "hash": "4a40886b85ea2cc4f0102b97b3009ee0d6b2eb9bf0dbb0b72d1cc14ebe67bdb8"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.25",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "The LORD {is} good unto them that wait for him, to the soul {that} seeketh him.",
    "hash": "e736495abb5b580eb73dd741e22df1c033b35fff60cc372fdf37dee39b56050a"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.26",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "{It is} good that {a man} should both hope and quietly wait for the salvation of the LORD.",
    "hash": "6aa4db0020b2fb123ef08c6b8e26889dd4106d92cc18dafed775154e586bac3e"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.27",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "{It is} good for a man that he bear the yoke in his youth.",
    "hash": "da74e534feff1b77f4ce6267f287e10c3357223f58259645b89f2fa075c085ee"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.28",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "He sitteth alone and keepeth silence, because he hath borne {it} upon him.",
    "hash": "c327a215d9c9a2224e15a86588852d8733015da57d3c9636c5e941bb4272a789"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.29",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "He putteth his mouth in the dust; if so be there may be hope.",
    "hash": "d184ee48f816a7caa75df5fc590fb1bf5ba6944c4209428914cf3ca6d52cde13"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.30",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "He giveth {his} cheek to him that smiteth him: he is filled full with reproach.",
    "hash": "be5530755fac52f5850e5ffa0acd3069144b1b911441f725840dd887d8ed5115"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.31",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 31,
    "text": "For the Lord will not cast off for ever:",
    "hash": "431b90bd132af977b4ff8c5b772798c79809fe7606e546b564d6ac15b744c1f3"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.32",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 32,
    "text": "But though he cause grief, yet will he have compassion according to the multitude of his mercies.",
    "hash": "da23987768777d400898856ac9389c3e8363b0d7781171f73bdeb24092832f01"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.33",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 33,
    "text": "For he doth not afflict willingly nor grieve the children of men. {willingly: Heb. from his heart}",
    "hash": "b861e52abefcf8c7303f86b463029a44c3dc991c14ea9c00144bfb5fffb87cdf"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.34",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 34,
    "text": "To crush under his feet all the prisoners of the earth,",
    "hash": "6004848716872652c132a5dfb89990cddeba9c94f6ec28d7eef6cb2c48359593"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.35",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 35,
    "text": "To turn aside the right of a man before the face of the most High, {the most High: or, a superior}",
    "hash": "b5b350728a34312397054113a565bc0f00429067c080ef7b762fc2206be7db1d"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.36",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 36,
    "text": "To subvert a man in his cause, the Lord approveth not. {approveth not: or, seeth not}",
    "hash": "bada9ba1f3e83dc6a022d2f8063a47ff9484384287610869b920094f18f0aee3"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.37",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 37,
    "text": "Who {is} he {that} saith, and it cometh to pass, {when} the Lord commandeth {it} not?",
    "hash": "293b61cf2de2d397465c2d2dcf5ad5af8313b34cb645f9fcf575dc31103fc79a"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.38",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 38,
    "text": "Out of the mouth of the most High proceedeth not evil and good?",
    "hash": "819b868187c096d9b5d03c341f50c8ca8842a4d8b4018a82313283027177f3c4"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.39",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 39,
    "text": "Wherefore doth a living man complain, a man for the punishment of his sins? {complain: or, murmur}",
    "hash": "b2db90ec48c94db525aa0d39b0f6849dfb339275b9e6f1f4fcdbd7b2d6ca5a52"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.40",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 40,
    "text": "Let us search and try our ways, and turn again to the LORD.",
    "hash": "eb81fa8e46c0e227e4c7dac79497d4a517b07932f438afb46e9271480dcd3319"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.41",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 41,
    "text": "Let us lift up our heart with {our} hands unto God in the heavens.",
    "hash": "ac72678e4de040eaa57081409fae0e138c47fdb68efade904d913b55c46b6a29"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.42",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 42,
    "text": "We have transgressed and have rebelled: thou hast not pardoned.",
    "hash": "00d51cd2dca22637d39f83bc2dc61988fcf18221e6625663090210e08b0e2c79"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.43",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 43,
    "text": "Thou hast covered with anger, and persecuted us: thou hast slain, thou hast not pitied.",
    "hash": "3e6fd9b68ed5728cbba433ec2d409a0a7d61bb6193418e1e704e52331ff1c238"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.44",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 44,
    "text": "Thou hast covered thyself with a cloud, that {our} prayer should not pass through.",
    "hash": "9981b1e2bced8be08908d83b28087f56ab82bb3d48c5ee0e1b9f758ac84a3484"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.45",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 45,
    "text": "Thou hast made us {as} the offscouring and refuse in the midst of the people.",
    "hash": "3affc770dc484ec6b98bcd4061a9a543ea8dadb2456923c1ce51608da19605c0"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.46",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 46,
    "text": "All our enemies have opened their mouths against us.",
    "hash": "33bd65826f107e62dabcb3e98b1497f7faae7588246845377ea4c2ca253bdf86"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.47",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 47,
    "text": "Fear and a snare is come upon us, desolation and destruction.",
    "hash": "f2fdd0a277883c708b50cad255f579b7f306cf166c6fd079894b9d220ce9468e"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.48",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 48,
    "text": "Mine eye runneth down with rivers of water for the destruction of the daughter of my people.",
    "hash": "fcd79924e79689257d26505fae82e885948d5607bb3fe19f835303d98797bc8a"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.49",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 49,
    "text": "Mine eye trickleth down, and ceaseth not, without any intermission,",
    "hash": "7a25910d0083cecdb2b24826ec548681ef53ee4617614a6e37110b7de5014473"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.50",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 50,
    "text": "Till the LORD look down, and behold from heaven.",
    "hash": "5e7c0f3f46e4dcdb3736ad52075c5908db4d072f46918e33c4a4c101ea325f6e"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.51",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 51,
    "text": "Mine eye affecteth mine heart because of all the daughters of my city. {mine heart: Heb. my soul} {because...: or, more than all}",
    "hash": "7c46148aad466d47b99196bbb00b13681432e4357ba389ab11e805944dccd096"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.52",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 52,
    "text": "Mine enemies chased me sore, like a bird, without cause.",
    "hash": "6775f1993ff1f15efefb8ab657dd55ea2a6e79147817b4d4e588414dd0cc12c3"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.53",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 53,
    "text": "They have cut off my life in the dungeon, and cast a stone upon me.",
    "hash": "27de5dec7075a7a76fe38c27dcd56078fa1a2a26efa4b720e42b3e98800c45ff"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.54",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 54,
    "text": "Waters flowed over mine head; {then} I said, I am cut off.",
    "hash": "1bd8f0caed87b3a6fd8d881a6782078a943b4d44f37298e52ba1a736ada534b8"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.55",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 55,
    "text": "I called upon thy name, O LORD, out of the low dungeon.",
    "hash": "a7a73698b2f7b8c9ee018143c9c528f800fb97a60c3b9b4a01a9aaa15f2b928d"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.56",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 56,
    "text": "Thou hast heard my voice: hide not thine ear at my breathing, at my cry.",
    "hash": "56a2c5a2738659b03c69899f43e35a3fbf73acfdcfc0afffa5a386168c5ae2af"
  },
  {
    "id": "LAM.3.57",
    "book": "Lamentations",
    "bookNum": 25,
    "bookAbbrev": "LAM",
    "chapter": 3,
    "verse": 57,
    "text": "Thou drewest near in the day {that} I called upon thee: thou saidst, Fear not.",
    "hash": "dfeb1782a20d7a161746892f388818fcd7e4868e59dc4e3f97552434982a66fc"
  },
  {
